The paper discusses data mining, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under several categories. However, given the focus on sequential pattern mining, the most likely category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also mentions applications such as web user analysis and natural language processing, which suggest a possible connection to cs.IR (information retrieval) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
